---
/**
 * Validated holdout results — the instrument panel. Six readouts from the
 * first_attempt_v1 evaluation, stated plainly. The win rate is the only
 * number allowed a status color; abstention is slate, never red.
 */
---

<section class="proof section" id="proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Validated holdout · first_attempt_v1</p>
      <h2 class="title">Tested on jobs it had never seen.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Trained on 12,398 real production records, then evaluated on 2,043
        future holdout jobs. Color Brain never invents a recipe — it retrieves
        one your factory already ran, only on the same substrate, and only when
        confident.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="proof__dashboard reveal">
      <article class="proof__primary">
        <p class="proof__kicker">Recommendation quality</p>
        <p class="proof__hero-value">86.7<span>%</span></p>
        <h3>of recommendations beat the technician's first attempt.</h3>
        <div class="proof__signal" aria-hidden="true">
          <i><b></b></i>
          <span>Validated wins</span>
          <strong>359 / 414</strong>
        </div>
      </article>

      <dl class="proof__grid">
        <div class="proof__cell proof__cell--protocol">
          <dt>Holdout protocol</dt>
          <dd><strong>2,043</strong> future jobs</dd>
          <dd><span>12,398</span> training records</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="proof__cell">
          <dt>Selective coverage</dt>
          <dd><strong>20.3%</strong></dd>
          <dd><span>414</span> recommendations</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="proof__cell">
          <dt>Median improvement</dt>
          <dd><strong>+0.2082</strong></dd>
          <dd>ΔE on recommended jobs</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="proof__cell proof__cell--quiet">
          <dt>Calibrated silence</dt>
          <dd><strong>~80%</strong></dd>
          <dd>withheld below confidence</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <p class="proof__footnote reveal">
      On the ~80% of jobs where Color Brain abstains, it is saying the evidence
      isn't strong enough to beat your technician's first attempt. Selectivity
      is the point — a recommendation you can trust.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .proof {
    background:
      linear-gradient(rgba(154, 163, 178, 0.035) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(154, 163, 178, 0.035) 1px, transparent 1px),
      var(--bg);
    background-size: 64px 64px;
  }

  .proof__dashboard {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.16fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .proof__primary {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 31rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    border: 1px solid rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at 60% 20%, rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.16), transparent 42%),
      linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(21, 24, 34, 0.96), rgba(10, 12, 17, 0.96));
  }

  .proof__primary::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 2rem;
    right: 2rem;
    width: 9rem;
    height: 9rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.15);
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 2rem rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.025),
      0 0 0 4rem rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.018);
  }

  .proof__kicker,
  .proof__cell dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .proof__hero-value {
    margin-top: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(5.5rem, 11vw, 9rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 0.8;
    letter-spacing: -0.06em;
    color: var(--win);
  }

  .proof__hero-value span {
    margin-left: 0.06em;
    font-size: 0.42em;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .proof__primary h3 {
    max-width: 20ch;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.2vw, 1.75rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .proof__signal {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .proof__signal i {
    height: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.12);
  }

  .proof__signal b {
    display: block;
    width: 86.7%;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--win);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.45);
  }

  .proof__signal strong {
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .proof__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .proof__cell {
    min-height: 14.875rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(15, 17, 24, 0.86);
  }

  .proof__cell dt {
    margin-bottom: auto;
  }

  .proof__cell dd {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .proof__cell dd strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .proof__cell dd span {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--ink-dim);
  }

  .proof__cell--quiet dd strong {
    color: var(--abstain);
  }

  @media (max-width: 940px) {
    .proof__dashboard {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .proof__primary {
      min-height: 27rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .proof__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .proof__cell {
      min-height: 12rem;
    }

    .proof__signal {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    }

    .proof__signal span {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  .proof__footnote {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
</style>
